{\rtf1\mac\ansicpg10000\cocoartf824\cocoasubrtf330 {\fonttbl\f0\fnil\fcharset77 LucidaGrande;\f1\fnil\fcharset77 LucidaGrande-Bold;} {\colortbl;\red255\green255\blue255;} \pard\tx560\tx1120\tx1680\tx2240\tx2800\tx3360\tx3920\tx4480\tx5040\tx5600\tx6160\tx6720\ql\qnatural\pardirnatural
\f0\fs14 \cf0 FlyMine is an integrated database of genomic, expression and protein data from Drosophila, Anopheles and other insects. As an integrated resource it is possible to run data mining queries that span domains of biological knowledge. Inclusion of InParanoid orthologues allows comparative analysis between organisms. \f1\b\fs19 \ \ \pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural \cf0 Quick Search \fs20 \
\fs12 \
\f0\b0\fs14 Enter any identifier, symbol or gene name in the search box on the FlyMine home page to access details pages and integrated tools. \fs16 \
\f1\b\fs14 \
\fs19 Browse Aspects \fs20 \
\fs12 \
\f0\b0\fs14 FlyMine presents data as 'aspects', with each aspect providing a view of a particular type of data (for example Gene Expression or Protein Interactions). Use the aspect icons on the FlyMine home page to run a predefined template query or to build your own query (see below). \fs20 \
\f1\b\fs14 \
\fs19 Run Template Queries \fs20 \
\fs12 \
\f0\b0\fs14 Dozens of useful queries have been predefined. These range from simple queries to retrieve a particular type of data to more complex queries that span the different types of data. Find lists of template queries on each aspect page or use the Template Search box on the home page and in the top menu. \fs16 \
\f1\b\fs14 \
\fs19 Use the FlyMine QueryBuilder \fs20 \
\fs12 \
\f0\b0\fs14 Advanced users can use a flexible query interface to construct their own data mining queries across the multiple integrated data sources, to modify existing template queries or to create new template queries. Access the FlyMine QueryBuilder via the home page or choose a query starting point on an aspect page. \fs16 \
\f1\b\fs14 \
\fs19 Operate on Lists \fs20 \
\fs12 \
\f0\b0\fs14 All queries in FlyMine can be performed on lists (or 'bags') that you create yourself. Bags can be created by typing or pasting in a list of identifiers, or uploading a file containing the list. Data from previous queries can also be saved into a bag using the boxes displayed underneath the query results. Saved bags of data can be used to constrain new queries, perform logical operations and can be exported. \fs16 \
\f1\b\fs14 \
\fs19 Save Queries \fs20 \
\fs12 \
\f0\b0\fs14 You can save your bags, queries and templates between sessions by creating an account using the 'Log in' box in the top menu on every page.}
